item.title: Zenith help
item.dc:creator: @llcoolchris llcoolchris
item.description:
@llcoolchris wrote:

Getting it online is one of the toughest parts for a new coder, and even an advanced one, you can’t just open up your router and port forward, turn on no-ip change client ip then turn on server, it is more advanced then that. there is issues that cause ports to be blocked, you have never port forwarded if you think it’s “simple” each time anyone port forwards it can take up to 4 hours just unblocking the programs.

item.title: Zenith help
item.dc:creator: @llcoolchris llcoolchris
item.description:
@llcoolchris wrote:

I’ve been through this a lot of times, I could not get it up and running, it is not just port forwarding you need to do, you also need to shut off any program that is blocking the port(firewall, anti virus, or even skype(although it uses port 80), on top of that you need to call you’re ISP (internet service provider) and ask them if they are blocking the port (which they do in some cases) it is a pain in the butt at times. I would suggest you get a VPS you still need to unblock ports on a VPS (turn off services and disable everything on internet explorer security wise) it’s a lot more then just port forwarding…
